SIMPLE: smatter
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Smatter
<hw>Smat"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>smateren</ets> to make a noise; cf. Sw. <ets>smattra</ets> to
clatter, to crackle, G. <ets>schmettern</ets> to dash, crash, to warble,
quaver.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To talk superficially or ignorantly; to
babble; to chatter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of state affairs you can not <qex>smatter</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To have a slight taste, or a slight, superficial
knowledge, of anything; to smack.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smatter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Smatter
<hw>Smat"ter</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To talk
superficially about.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To gain a slight taste of; to acquire a slight,
superficial knowledge of; to smack.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smatter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Smatter
<hw>Smat"ter</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Superficial knowledge; a
smattering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smatterer</ent>⟦br⟧
